(491, '**Dhairen - Maybe for DeVC; Clear no for fund considering founder archetype**: Spikey 1, especially considering he is a 21 yo building in fintech - ++ High agency and strong clarity of thought for a 21-year-old founder ++ Outside in, numerate and analytical - tracking all the right metrics, sahi customer reviews mining, thinking about the right expansion levers - ++ Outside in, numerate and analytical - tracking all the right metrics, sahi customer reviews mining, thinking about the right expansion levers - ?? Don''t love the product, don''t see any edge and app is glitchy - ?? Is there a real product edge or is it just an ICP play - ?? Quality of user - 3k CAC, 8-10k ARPU are not top tier metrics; also, how much can one sweat this ICP? **Meeting Notes** **Company Overview & Current Status** - Trackk - AI-first mobile trading platform targeting Gen Z (18-30 age group) - Youngest company to receive direct broking license (obtained 4 months ago) - Previously operated as sub-broker, now direct exchange registration - Founded when CEO was 18, now 21 years old (5-year journey) - Current metrics and traction: - 1.3 lakh total signups on platform - 30,000 DMAT accounts opened during sub-broker period - ~1 lakh trades processed monthly (when sub-broker) - 90% user retention on current insights platform - 85% of user base acquired are first-time traders - Funding round structure - looking to raise ~$3-3.5M at $13M post **Platform Architecture & Technology Stack** - Core technology built...'),
(493, 'Notes from @Yashasvi Madhogaria as of 2024-08-20: Adding the notes, deck and latest update from Tradeface – another company building in retailer supply chain with a vision to leverage ONDC – have started with a small pilot **AS Views: (as of December’23)** Overall: PWC as Maybe on founder, but extremely low margin, competitive and commoditised business. - +Good pedigree teams. Classic EOs - +Insightful, 2 order thinking + outside in nd - + Commercial – whole thesis is based on doing wholesales online but profitably - ? Low margins – Udaan business essentially and subscale – no clear margin expansion lever - ? No real tech moat in the business, ONDC as an enabler but not core - ? Monetization and value prop **Meeting notes** [Sebastian](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sebastiangvempeny/?original_referer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F&originalSubdomain=in) - 19 years of experience - Started with Citibank – liabilities, sales etc. - Metro cash and carry – was leading the trader(reseller business) - Then moved to Udaan – trade marketing for 3 years [Shivaram](https://www.linkedin.com/in/shivramdega/?originalSubdomain=in) - Tech guy, ex Co Founder of Xero Apps - Engineering Team lead at Paytm Insider (3 yrs) - Software Architect at Capital Float (4 yrs) [Vaibhav](https://www.linkedin.com/in/vaibhav-verma-16a1115/?originalSubdomain=in'') - Ex head of pricing at Udaan (3 yrs) - Senior GM of Pricing at Metro cash and carry (10 yrs) - NMIMS MBA Problem: - Earlier Kiraanas were family busi...')
